// Zero-mentions check — same query used by the Bicep alert-zero-mentions rule.
// Fires (returns 0 rows) when /mentions received no non-4xx requests in 24 h.
// A fully silent /mentions endpoint usually means the X Account Activity
// subscription was revoked or the bot's OAuth access token expired.
//
// Run manually to investigate after receiving the alert:
//   - If this returns rows, the alert was a false positive (webhook is alive).
//   - If no rows, check X dev portal → webhook subscriptions and token validity.

AppRequests
| where TimeGenerated > ago(24h)
| where Url contains "/mentions"
| where not(ResultCode startswith "4")
| project TimeGenerated, ResultCode, DurationMs, Url
| order by TimeGenerated desc
